Two bombs explode in the central Nigerian city of Jos with at least 40 people dead. (Reuters via Daily Mail)Russian forces reportedly begin combat operations in Syria in support of the Bashar al-Assad government. (Reuters)According to the Syrian Observatory for Human Rights, a series of air-raids by the Syrian Arab Air Force on the rebel-held market town of Douma kills at least 110 people and leaves hundreds injured. (BBC), (The International Business Times), (Reuters), (Xinhua), (Al Jazeera)